---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CTA from "../components/CTA.astro";
import { getCollection } from "astro:content";

const apps = await getCollection("apps");
const live = apps.filter(a => a.data.status === "live").length;
const soon = apps.filter(a => a.data.status === "coming-soon").length;
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Investors - Win-Win Apps"
  description="Portfolio thesis, velocity, team and exit path for Win-Win Apps, an indie Shopify app studio."
  current="investors"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">Investors</p>
      <h1>A portfolio of simple Shopify apps.</h1>
      <p class="hero-lead">We build small, focused Shopify apps, ship fast, and stack them into a cashflow-positive portfolio. Low overhead, lean backends, exit optionality.</p>
      <div class="stat-strip" style="margin-top:32px">
        <div class="stat-item"><strong>{live}</strong><span>Live apps</span></div>
        <div class="stat-item"><strong>{soon}</strong><span>In pipeline</span></div>
        <div class="stat-item"><strong>100</strong><span>App blueprint</span></div>
        <div class="stat-item"><strong>3-5x</strong><span>ARR exit multiple</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container-narrow prose">
      <h2>Thesis</h2>
      <p>The Shopify App Store has 8,000+ apps but the long tail of mid-volume categories is poorly served. Most top apps are overpriced, overbuilt, and slow to ship. We target niches where 2 to 5 apps split the market and the leaders have obvious 1-2 star complaints. We enter with a free tier that covers what they gate behind 9 to 29 dollars a month.</p>

      <h2>Why this works</h2>
      <p>Every Win-Win app has a real backend, but we push as much of the app into Shopify's own infrastructure as we can. Theme app extensions render on the storefront inside the theme itself. Shopify metafields hold merchant config. Our server handles OAuth, admin UI, bulk operations, and the bits Shopify cannot handle natively.</p>
      <p>That split lets us run each app on a small Fly.io deployment with a modest Postgres database. No scale-out email infrastructure, no queue fleet, no CDN bills. The difference between an app costing $10 a month to operate and one costing $1,000 a month compounds across a portfolio of fifty apps.</p>

      <h2>Velocity</h2>
      <p>Our target is 10 new apps per month, each going from research to shipped in 3 days. We currently have {live} live, {soon} in the pipeline, and a 100-app blueprint mapped across conversion, merchandising, loyalty, fulfillment, and operations categories.</p>

      <h2>Exit path</h2>
      <p>Shopify apps trade on the secondary market at 3 to 5x ARR for healthy portfolios. Single apps with 1k+ installs and a clean review profile sell as drop-in acquisitions to larger app studios or private buyers. Our portfolio design means any subset can be sold independently, and the roll-up buyer community is active.</p>

      <h2>Current portfolio</h2>
      <p>Product Badges and Bulk Store Credit are live on the Shopify App Store. Next shipments are in delivery date estimation and country-of-origin badges. Full app list and status is on <a href="/apps/">our apps page</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">Team</p>
        <h2>A merchant and a builder.</h2>
        <p>Omar Shahban, CEO, is a Shopify merchant of more than a decade with over $20M in global Shopify revenue. Shane Stratton, CTO, is a senior engineer with experience at Amazon, IBM and Chess.com.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:18px"><a href="/team/" class="btn btn-secondary">Meet the team</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <CTA
        heading="Want to talk?"
        body="If you invest in indie software studios, portfolio SaaS, or Shopify ecosystem plays, reach out directly."
        primaryLabel="omar@wwapps.io"
        primaryHref="mailto:omar@wwapps.io"
      />
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

